{"cursor":"4179","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\nA region is 'arid' when it is characterized by a severe lack of available water,\nto the extent of hindering or preventing the growth and development of plant and\nanimal life. Environments subject to arid climates tend to lack vegetation and\nare called xeric or desertic. Most \"arid\" climates surround the equator; these\nplaces include most of Africa and parts of South America and Central America.\n","linknr":148,"url":"Arid","recorded":1362372141,"links":46,"instances":["meteorology"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Climatology"],"headings":["Concepts","Geographical distribution","Change over time","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1c/Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg/20px-Wiki_letter_w_cropped.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["precipitation","meteorology"]],"members":["precipitation"],"related":["Individual_growth","Morphogenesis","Deserts_and_xeric_shrublands","Desert","Africa","South_America","Central_America","Permanent_wilting_point","Water_vapor","Lichen","Xerophytes","Climax_vegetation","Land_use","Precipitation_(meteorology)","Surface_runoff","Evapotranspiration","Aridity_index","Semi-arid","Rain_shadow","Atacama_Desert","Atmosphere","Climate_change","Aridification","Desert_climate","Desiccation_tolerance","Drought","Relative_humidity","Saturation_vapor_pressure"]}